===Etymology===
From a wide variety of {{etyl|enm|en}} forms including {{term|hevin|lang=enm}}, {{term|heuen|lang=enm}}, {{term|hewin||heaven, sky|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|enm}} {{term|heofon||heaven, sky|lang=ang}} of uncertain etymology.<ref name=oed/>

Cognate with {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|heven|hēven|heaven, sky|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|heƀan||heaven, sky|lang=osx}}, and possibly the rare {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|hifinn|lang=non}}, probably [[dissimilation|dissimilated]] forms of the Germanic root appearing in {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|himinn||heaven, sky|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌷𐌹𐌼𐌹𐌽𐍃||tr=himins|heaven, sky|lang=got}}, {{etyl|gmq-osw|-}} {{term|himin|lang=gmq-osw}}, {{etyl|gmq-oda|-}} {{term|himæn|lang=gmq-oda}} and the probable variants appearing in {{etyl|osx|-}}, {{etyl|odt|-}}, and {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|himil|lang=odt}} (Modern {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|hemel|lang=nl}} and {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Himmel|lang=de}}).<ref name=oed/>

From these cognates, some scholars propose a further derivation from {{etyl|gem-pro|ang}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*himinaz}} or {{term/t|gem-pro|*himilaz||heaven, sky}}; from {{etyl|ine-pro|gem-pro}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*k(')em-en-}} or {{term/t|ine-pro|*k(')em-er-||sky, cloud}}; from {{etyl|ine-pro|-}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*ḱam-||cover, shroud, clothes}}.{{rfv-etymology|lang=en}}<!--Kindly don't remove without a source. The OED discusses a slightly different Proto-Germanic root; the point stands but it doesn't support the current reconstructions presented here.--> Such a derivation would be cognate with [[shame]].<ref name=oed/>

